%N A199401 Decimal expansion of constant Product_{p>=3} (1 - (-1)^((p-1)/2)/(p-1)). Hardy-Littlewood constant of x^2 + 1.
%C A199401 Arises in studying A002496.
%C A199401 The constant is Product_{primes p} (1-chi(p)/(p-1)) where chi is the Dirichlet character A101455. Its Euler expansion is (1/(L(m=4,r=2,s=1)* zeta(m=4,n=3,s=2)) *Product_{s>=2} zeta(m=4,n=1,s)^gamma(s), where L and zeta are the functions tabulated in arXiv:1008.2547 and gamma is the sequence A001037. In particular L(m=4,r=2,s=1) = A003881 and zeta(m=4,n=1,s=2)=A175647. - _R. J. Mathar_, Nov 29 2011
